Package: fernsicht
Type: Package
Title: Watch Your R Code's Progress From Anywhere
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person(
    given = "Thomas",
    family = "Konstantinovsky",
    email = "thomaskon90@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")
  )
Description: Wrap your long-running loops with blick() and share a live
    progress URL with anyone in the world. Progress flows peer-to-peer
    via WebRTC DataChannels, so the data stays between you and your
    viewers. The package wraps the fernsicht-bridge Go binary, which is
    lazy-downloaded from GitHub releases on first use.
License: AGPL-3 + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/MuteJester/Fernsicht,
    https://app.fernsicht.space/
BugReports: https://github.com/MuteJester/Fernsicht/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Language: en-US
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    processx (>= 3.8.0),
    jsonlite (>= 1.8.0),
    R6 (>= 2.5.0),
    digest (>= 0.6.30)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.2.0),
    withr (>= 2.5.0),
    httpuv (>= 1.6.0),
